	<div id="id1879" class="post">
		<h2 class="title"><span class="image-wrapper"><img height="45" alt="Rules of flight" width="182" class="title" src="../../../resources/net.databinder.components.RenderedLabel/c408ec59"/><span class="title">Rules of flight</span></span></h2>
		<div class="byline"><span>
			<span>By <span class="alias">Doctor Barnett</span>, <span>on February 10, 2006</span></span>
			<span id="id187a" class="tags">
					{&nbsp;<span><a href="../../../city/tag/flying/#selected-tag"><span>flying</span></a></span>&nbsp;}
			</span>
		</span></div>
		<div><p style="float:right"><img src="/pictures/clasp.jpg" alt="" /></p>


	<p><em><span class="caps">NEW YORK EDITION</span></em></p>


	<ol>
	<li><strong>Always fly from LaGuardia for domestic.</strong> Unless you&#8217;re going to a place where they speak a different language, have perfect weather, or still like Michael Jackson, <span class="caps">JFK</span> and Newark simply aren&#8217;t worth the  trip.</li>
		<li><strong>Do not fly Delta from LaGuardia.</strong> Do you really want to get into a fight with that wild-haired gate agent queen <em>again</em>?</li>
		<li><strong>Take the subway and bus to <span class="caps">LGA</span>.</strong> It&#8217;s faster, less nausea-inducing, and vastly cheaper than taking a taxi.</li>
		<li><strong>Take the AirTrain to <span class="caps">JFK</span> or Newark.</strong> Duh. The AirTrain is the the bomb. (Don&#8217;t take that the wrong way.)</li>
		<li><strong>Don&#8217;t ask for the exit row.</strong> Leave them for <a href="/eat">MrLittlePants</a>. He&#8217;s very tall and gets grumpy if <em>you&#8217;ve</em> already taken his seat.</li>
		<li><strong>If your flight is greatly delayed or cancelled, take the refund.</strong> Seriously, don&#8217;t let them bully you around like that. Spend the money on another carrier, or a large screen T.V. and DVDs of the place you were <em>hoping</em> to go for that long weekend.</li>
		<li><strong>Loathe the <span class="caps">TSA</span>.</strong> They will never be able to <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A15183-2004Dec20.html">follow</a> their own simple <a href="http://www.tsa.gov/public/interapp/editorial/editorial_1050.xml">shoe policy</a>. They are lower than dogs.</li>
		<li><strong>Expect the worst.</strong> Be pleasantly surprised! (Or smugly, angrily accurate.)</li>
		<li><strong>Do as you&#8217;re told&#8212;follow along in the damn flight safety card.</strong> Which picture is your favorite? Ours is of course the flashed-out swimming drag-queen stewardess <em>(pictured above)</em>.</li>
		<li><strong>Flight attendant cross check.</strong> One L one R! Two L two R!</li>
	</ol></div>
